

-- the currently used initial guess is annoying and poor: One inputs a number
of MOs expanded in the chosen atom centred basis set in the structure
definition.  Default is coeffs of zero and one, which is extremely poor for
almost all structures.

There is some functionality coded in initial_guess.F90 but it seems not to be
used at the moment.

Implementing something Hueckel-like or h1 would be an obvious first choice.


